        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued September 4 at 5:44PM MST until September 4 at 6:00PM MST by NWS Phoenix AZ</headline>
        <description>At 544 PM MST, a severe thunderstorm was located near Mohawk, or 41
miles east of Fortuna Foothills, moving west at 10 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Mohawk.

This includes AZ Interstate 8 between mile markers 45 and 68.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
